A vintage-style illustration showing a single computer monitor fragmenting into dozens of floating rectangular screens, each displaying the same website but with subtle visual distortions and variations. The screens cascade outward in a spiral pattern against a warm sepia-toned background with faded grid paper texture. Some screens appear crisp and perfect while others show broken layouts, misaligned elements, and color shifts. Small magnifying glasses hover near several screens, examining the differences. The overall composition suggests the frustration and complexity of visual consistency, rendered in muted oranges, browns, and cream colors with hand-drawn crosshatching details reminiscent of 1950s technical illustrations.
